(12088, 1, '2015-09-03 06:06:11', '2015-09-03 06:06:11', '[fullwidth_text title="SCHOOL AND ACADEMIC ADMINISTRATION" alt_background="none" el_class="adjust1" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The school is administratively opened Monday to Friday between the hours of 7.30am and 5.00pm; except weekends and public holidays.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Academic activities begin for all levels and classes with a moral building and informative assembly by 7.30am; after which all class subject activities commence. There are in between class subject activities commencement and closing, the short and long break periods that provide both the learners and the teachers the frontage to refresh themselves.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The school adopts the broad based national curriculum blended with British curriculum; employing the Montessori concept in instructional delivery.</p>\r\n[/fullwidth_text] [spb_text_block title="ACADEMIC CALENDAR" pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The school runs the approved government academic scheme of work and calendar; e.g three terms in one academic year. There is usually one full week mid term break in every term in line with approved standard for schools/colleges with international nomenclature.</p>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [spb_text_block title="STAFF DEVELOPMENT" pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">At Solid Steps International School, we take staff development seriously, as it is fundamental in providing the students with the best possible education. The various staff development programmes undertaken by the school provides teachers with the skills and strategies to deliver consistently outstanding lessons.The focus is on high quality ongoing assessment (checking and consolidation of learning), high quality planning and high quality feedback to ensure progression in learning for all learners.</p>\r\n[/spb_text_block]', 'School Administration', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'school-administration', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:38:49', '2015-09-04 05:38:49', '', 0, 'http://localhost/mine/SolidSteps/?page_id=12088', 0, 'page', '', 0),
