gh quality feedback to ensure progression in learning for all learners.</p>\r\n[/spb_text_block]', 'School Administration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12088-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:38:49', '2015-09-04 05:38:49', '', 12088, 'http://localhost/mine/SolidSteps/2015/09/04/12088-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(12136, 1, '2015-09-04 05:41:23', '2015-09-04 05:41:23', '[fullwidth_text alt_background="none" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<p class="head1" style="text-align: center;">Statement of Solid Steps International Schools Ethos</p>\r\n<p class="parag" style="text-align: center;">Our philosophy at Solid Steps International School is simple. Provide a secure, purposeful environment, deliver first class teaching that inspires and challenges and celebrate each child for who they are and what they do.</p>\r\n[/fullwidth_text] [boxed_content type="coloured" custom_bg_colour="#F0FFF0" custom_text_colour="#000" pb_margin_bottom="no" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">We are a forward-thinking school aiming to prepare our children and students for a rapidly changing world by equipping them with critical thinking skills, global perspective, and respect for core values of honesty, loyalty, and compassion. Developing these skills is the corner stone of the education we offer.Students will have success for today and be prepared for tomorrow.</p>\r\n[/boxed_content] [fullwidth_text title="SOLID STEPS INTERNATIONAL SCHOOL''S AIMS" alt_background="none" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<h3 class="aim-color">Teaching and Learning</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">To provide excellence and learning across all subjects.</li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">Inspirational Staff who celebrates each child for their individuality and achievements.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class="aim-color">Standards and Expectations</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">To motivate through a challenging environment that fosters creativity, curiosity and confidence.</li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">By setting high expectations for each and every boy and girl tracking their progress to ensure to ensure they gain the highest qualification alongside a wealth of other skills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class="aim-color">Self-Development and Adaptability</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">To encourage boys and girls to be resilient, flexible and adaptable by providing them with situations that develop their capacity to respond in novel situations.</li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">To encourage staff with the desire to reflect on their practice, learn new skills, show innovation and be adaptable to change.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class="aim-color">Communication</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">To inspire our boys and girls in acquiring the art, skills and confidence to communicate with clarity with both spoken and written word.</li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">To inspire a community in which everyone is respectful of others and understands how to communicate appropriately; in particular social media.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 class="aim-color">The Business of Education</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">To instil in our boys and girls an appreciation that a significant investment has been made in their education by both parents and school; and tat with privilege comes responsibility.</li>\r\n	<li style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">To instil a sense of commitment in our boys,girls and staff to promote their school a s ambassadors to ensure its continued success as a school which offers and excellent education for young people and an excellent working environment for staff..</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/fullwidth_text]', 'Aims and Ethos', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12079-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-04 05:41:23', '2015-09-04 05:41:23', '', 12079, 'http://localhost/mine/SolidSteps/2015/09/04/12079-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
