ghest levels of achievement, effort and behaviour from all our pupils/students. We maximize student attainment, provide support, welfare and inspiration in a secure and healthy environment, committed to continuous improvement. Our students will be confident, successful and able to contribute effectively and responsibly to society. Our school''s motto ''Taking Solid Steps into academic success with the home zone advantage'' stems from our belief that success can only come through a close partnership between dedicated staff, confident students, supportive parents and a committed Management Team. We look forward to working with you to enable your child to achieve their full potential.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 16px;">We are proud of our record of building positive relationships between students, and between staff and students. We always seek to share our values with all members of the school and the wider community. Involving students families in monitoring and promoting progress is a vital part of what we do, and we are always looking for new and better ways to communicate, because we know that when student, school and family work together, we can create the power to drive achievement.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: -4px;">Mrs Okpor, J.I.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style="color: #3465aa;">Proprietress and Director of Studies</h4>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_row] [testimonial_slider title="Testimonials" text_size="large" item_count="6" order="date" category="home" autoplay="yes" alt_background="alt-three" el_class="mt0 mb0 bb0 bt0 testi-space" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-12 16:13:16', '2015-09-12 16:13:16', '', 2, 'http://localhost/mine/SolidSteps/2015/09/12/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(12203, 1, '2015-09-12 17:23:00', '2015-09-12 17:23:00', '[fullwidth_text title="VINTAGE LOCATION" alt_background="none" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Our school is situated in 7-9 Williams Bademosi Street, Off Governor Road, Emmanuel Bus Stop, Ikotun, Lagos Nigeria. Our school is advantageously located occupying wide expanse of land. It is flanked by the Diamond Estate on the south pole, the Greenland Estate on the east pole, the Governor Road that connects the Alimosho Local Government Council Headquarters at Ikotun on the west pole and Ikotun-Egbeda Road on the north pole. It has easy access and link from the LASU-Isheri Road through Odo-Eran Bus Stop.</p>\r\n[/fullwidth_text] [fullwidth_text title="ESTABLISHMENT HISYORY" alt_background="none" width="1/1" el_position="first last"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The school formally began operations on 5th August 2013 during the summer coaching; which was used to successfully test run our entire plant and facilities. However, we need to state that our decision to invest and launch into education was never borne from any imagination for golden fleece but the sheer and innate passion to empower mankind; using education as a veritable tool. It took us over five years to conduct effective research both at home and overseas, to appraise the intricacies inherent in educational investment, management and administration. Similarly, all necessary legal requirements were complied with prior to commencement of operation, such as registration with the Corporate Affairs Commission, name search and approval with the Lagos State Ministry of Education, among others. Over the years a lot has changed for but one thing has remained consistent: a focus on helping your child discover and develop their unique talents within a disciplined and caring environment.</p>\r\n[/fullwidth_text] [spb_row wrap_type="content-width" row_bg_type="color" row_bg_color="#faebd7" color_row_height="content-height" bg_type="cover" parallax_image_height="content-height" parallax_image_movement="fixed" parallax_image_speed="0.5" parallax_video_height="window-height" parallax_video_overlay="none" row_overlay_opacity="0" row_padding_vertical="65" row_padding_horizontal="4" row_margin_vertical="0" remove_element_spacing="no" inner_column_height="col-natural" row_el_class="row-color" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_icon_box title="SCHOOL MOTTO" box_type="standard" character="A" color="standard" target="_self" animation="none" animation_delay="0" width="1/3" el_position="first"]\r\n\r\n<strong style="color: #000; font-size: 16px;">Taking Solid Steps into academic success with the home zone advantage.</strong>\r\n\r\n[/spb_icon_box] [spb_icon_box title="MISSION STATEMENT" box_type="standard" character="B" color="standard" target="_self" animation="none" animation_delay="0" width="1/3"]\r\n\r\n<strong style="color: #000; font-size: 16px;">To assert that academic excellence and glory can be achieved without malpractice.</strong>\r\n\r\n[/spb_icon_box] [spb_icon_box title="OUR VISION" box_type="standard" character="C" color="standard" target="_self" animation="none" animation_delay="0" width="1/3" el_position="last"]\r\n\r\n<strong style="color: #000; font-size: 16px;">To raise leaders and champions that would create positive and noticeable difference in the society.</strong>\r\n\r\n[/spb_icon_box] [/spb_row] [blank_spacer height="30px" width="1/1" el_position="first last"] [spb_text_block title="OUR SCHOOL CHARACTER &amp; UNIFORMS" pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/2" el_position="first"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">The uniform reflects the school character and greatly contributes to a childs sense of belonging and pride in their school. The school colors are navy blue and white. Solid Steps international schools pinafores, shorts, shirts, blouses, polo shirts, cardigans, books and bags all bearing the schools branding are on sale at the school offices</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Please note that nail varnish, make up, colored hair, hair beads and bold jewellery are deemed inappropriate for school. All clothing, bags, pencil cases, flasks and bottles must be clearly named. Mobile phones, iPods, computer games, toys etc. shall not be permitted in school.</p>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [spb_text_block title="HEALTH &amp; SAFETY" pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/2" el_position="last"]\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We want to be known as a healthy school and we encourage healthy lifestyles and healthy eating. We have facilities to provide healthy and balanced diets for the children and we encourage parents if they wish to pack lunches for their children to ensure healthy diets too.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">At Solid Steps, we ensure that all adults working at the school are committed to safeguarding our children, we observe safety measures at all times</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">First aid boxes are available at the school with trained staff to administer . Specific teachers and teaching assistants are trained to administer first aid treatments, if and when required.</p>\r\n[/spb_text_block] [spb_text_block title="OUR SCHOOL PLEDGE" pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/2" el_position="first"]\r\n\r\n<dl class="ic-txt"><dt>I pledge to Solid Steps my school\r\nTo be diligent, obedient and honest\r\nTo study well to be a leader and champion\r\nTo serve as a shinning example to my peers\r\nTo assert that academic excellence can be achieved without malpractice\r\nAnd create positive difference in the society\r\nSo help me God</dt><dd></dd></dl>[/spb_text_block] [spb_text_block title="OUR SCHOOL ANTHEM" pb_margin_bottom="no" pb_border_bottom="no" width="1/2" el_position="last"]\r\n\r\n<dl class="ic-txt"><dt>Solid Steps\r\nAn academy established by vision from God\r\nWhere the Leaders and Champions are raised\r\nTo lead while others follow\r\nTo command while others obey</dt></dl><dl class="ic-txt"><dt>We shall rule\r\nWe shall lead\r\nWe shall excel\r\nWhere others fail</dt></dl>[/spb_text_block]', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12023-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-09-12 17:23:00', '2015-09-12 17:23:00', '', 12023, 'http://localhost/mine/SolidSteps/2015/09/12/12023-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
